Dan You are incorrect. Jim no longer owns TheStreet which has been sold to The Maven. He writes a column for TheStreet, just as I do. Do your homework better.

Today's comments by @jimcramer to Speaker Nancy Pelosi were taken totally out of context by the many in the media and outside the media. I have been writing a column alongside Jim for 23 years on @realmoney and I know Jim professionally as well as anyone. To suggest his was an

attack on the Speaker of the House is not only patently absurd but indicates that those have no knowledge about Jim's respect for her and the office that she represents. It seems everyone is looking for a "gotcha" moment - well, people are looking under the wrong rock here.

I have admired Jim up close for over the last two decades. He is more sensitive, more respectful, more intelligent, more charitable and a more compassionate person than the haters represent and have any concept of. To me he is a role model as an educator, commentator, husband
